## 💾 Storage Schema (`backend/storage.py`)

DebateX utilizes file-based JSON persistence in the directory `data/conversations/`. 

```json
{
  "id": "uuid-v4-string",
  "created_at": "ISO-8601-UTC-timestamp",
  "title": "Short Summarized Title",
  "messages": [
    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "User query text"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "stage1": [ { "model": "...", "response": "..." } ],
      "stage2": [ { "model": "...", "ranking": "...", "parsed_ranking": [...] } ],
      "stage3": { "model": "...", "response": "..." },
      "rounds": [
        { "round": 1, "type": "initial_answers", "data": [...] },
        { "round": 2, "type": "peer_review", "data": [...] },
        { "round": 3, "type": "revise_or_defend", "data": [...] },
        { "round": 4, "type": "challenger", "data": {...} },
        { "round": 5, "type": "chairman_synthesis", "data": {...} }
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "label_to_model": { "Response A": "groq/qwen/qwen3-32b", ... },
        "aggregate_rankings": [ { "model": "...", "average_rank": 1.5, ... } ]
      }
    }
  ]
}
```
*Note: Models evaluate each other anonymized. The de-anonymization mapping (`label_to_model`) is stored in metadata and resolved dynamically in the UI.*
